folder: Jumel Terrace & Sylvan Terrace, Manhattan, NY
text:
(I)
Jumel Terrace,West Side and North of Sylvan Terrace. Jumel Terrace is so named from Stephen Jumel,who bought the surrounding property in I8I0. Jumel Terrace is a short Street running paralell to Amsterdam
Avenue,from West I60th to I62nd Street.
On the East side is the old Jumel Mansion and Roger Morris Park,the latter named for Captain Roger Morris,who built the house in I758.

folder: Sylvan Terrace & Jumel Terrace, Manhattan, NY
text:
Sylvan Terrace (formerly Sylvan Place), west from Jumel Terrace. This little block of wooden houses, terminating in an elevation on the east side of St. Nicholas Avenue, was a real estate development of the early 1880's, when this part of town was still suburban. See also Jumel Terrace, and St. Nicholas Avenue, east side from 160th to 162nd Streets. The building in the background is on the west side of St. Nicholas Avenue.

October 12, 1934
P.L. Sperr

Sylvan Terrace still exists today.
title: Manhattan: Sylvan Terrace - Jumel Terrace
